The paper presents a new algorithm for solving linear complementarity problems (LCPs) with a particular special structure, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and optimization (cs.Optimization). The algorithm uses interior-point potential-reduction techniques, which are commonly used in optimization (cs.Optimization) and have been applied to LCPs in previous work. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the algorithm, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.DS, cs.DC). Finally, the paper presents numerical experiments to demonstrate the effectiveness of the algorithm, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves empirical evaluation of an algorithm.
